divs: Sighting DetailsI was at work taking a moment to look at the stars (since this was the first clear night we have had in 2 weeks) When I saw an object pass. The object had no discernable shape, there were two dim lights on the object and that���s the only visible part of it. The reason I believe this was one object and not two was due to the way in which it moved. The best way I can describe it would be to imagine a pen with a light on each end, and as the object moved though the sky it wobbled from side to side. The object moved at a relatively fast pace to the south until I lost site of it. Now I consider myself a relatively level headed person, I know this wasn���t a satellite, airplane, shooting star or a fireball. I spend a lot of time looking at the stars, and this was something I can say I have never seen before.
Summary: Unknown object flying over Peoria IL
